This code is used to check statics on table :

sp_helpstats N'Employee','ALL'   // This code is used to check all statics object exists on table Employee

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This code is used to set table statistics on or off:

generally this code is used to check logic read , physical read 

set STATISTICS io ON

set STATISTICS io OFF

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This code is used to create or set statistics object of table or on spefic columb

EXEC sp_autostats 'dbo.Employee';  // This code is used to check autostats is enabled or not

EXEC sp_autostats 'dbo.Employee', 'ON'   //  This code is used to on autostats of table dbo.Employee

EXEC sp_autostats 'dbo.Employee', 'OFF'  //  This code is used to off autostats of table dbo.Employee

EXEC sp_autostats 'dbo.Employee', 'ON', PK__Employee__3214EC27826760CD;   //  This code is used to on autostats  with specific static object name

EXEC sp_autostats 'dbo.Employee', 'OFF', PK__Employee__3214EC27826760CD;    //  This code is used to off autostats  with specific static object name

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This command is used to check sql pages of table 

DBCC IND('DailySqlStudy',Employee,-1)

DBCC TRACEON(3604)
DBCC PAGE('DailySqlStudy',1,282,1)
            
